aa(lp68
VIf we imagine quantum mechanics or quantum physics, then,
p69
aVas the fundamental foundation of reality itself,
p70
aVthen it's not surprising that we say
p71
aVquantum physics underpins organic chemistry.
p72
aVAfter all, it gives us the rules that tell us
p73
aVhow the atoms fit together to make organic molecules.
p74
aVOrganic chemistry, scaled up in complexity,
p75
aVgives us molecular biology, which of course leads to life itself.
p76
aVSo in a way, it's sort of not surprising.
p77
aVIt's almost trivial.
p78
aVYou say, "Well, of course life ultimately must depend of quantum mechanics."
