aVIt was tremendously influential.
p133
aVIt influenced Francis Crick and James Watson,
p134
aVthe discoverers of the double-helix structure of DNA.
p135
aVTo paraphrase a description in the book, he says:
p136
aVAt the molecular level, living organisms have a certain order,
p137
aVa structure to them that's very different
p138
aVfrom the random thermodynamic jostling of atoms and molecules
p139
aVin inanimate matter of the same complexity.
